From a88bf67a1754dbce821116711c73a366aeace9d8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: poeggi <48416618+poeggi@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Fri, 12 Jun 2026 17:36:45 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 10/12] feat: auto-detect local address from REMOTE_ADDR; ifs=
 now optional override

Replace hardcoded ifs=/address= config with protocol-aware auto-detection:
- detect_local_address() uses REMOTE_ADDR + connect() trick to find the
  outbound local IP matching the client's protocol (IPv4 or IPv6)
- Loopback clients (local proxy) fall back to WSD multicast connect trick
- ifs= config option kept as optional override (same semantics as -i in
  wsd_simple_server): when set, address and MAC both come from that interface
- All service files (device, events, media, media2) use service_ctx.address_url
  for URL construction instead of calling get_ip_address() per request
- GetNetworkInterfaces keeps get_ip_address() for netmask/prefix-length
- conf.example and JSON example updated: ifs= commented out as optional
---
